Function: algethassei
Section: algebras
C-Name: algethassei
Prototype: G
Help: algethassei(al): the hasse invariant of the central simple algebra al at infinite places.
Doc: Given a central simple algebra \var{al} output by \tet{alinit}, returns a \typ{VECSMALL} $h_i$ of $r_1$ integers modulo the degree $d$ of \var{al}, where $r_1$ is the number of real places of the center: the local Hasse invariants of \var{al} at infinite places.
 \bprog
 ? nf = nfinit(y^2-5);
 ? A = alinit(nf, [-1,y]);
 ? algethassei(A)
 %3 = Vecsmall([1, 0])
 @eprog
